Put your Empty Pages in the Celestial Globe before you click 'Contemplate the heavens'.

Warning: The Celestial Globe can only be used by the Theologer. You can attempt it without training but that only has a 10% chance to succeed. Check the forums for more information about jobs.
* Knowledge from certain artifacts and empty pages

Put your Papyrus or Empty Pages in the desk before you click 'Process these items'.

Alternatively you can put ONE item generated by the job system in the desk and change its name or description by saying these lines (the part between the quotes) in the SHOUT channel:

"ds_j name The Book of Days" (this changes the name of the item into "The Book of Days"
"ds_j bio A fancy calendar" (this changes the description of the item into "A fancy calendar"
"ds_j append With Dirty Pictures!" (this adds With Dirty Pictures!" at the end of the description)

You can store up to 20 Bone Wands in this holder. Mind that this does not work with enchanted wands or any other wand types, only unenchanted Bone Wands.

Use the holder on a wand to store it. You can also use the wand case on a container and you'll store all the suitable wands in it in one go.

Use the holder on yourself to recreate wands. It will always produce 1 wand per use.

This description will be replaced by the number of wands stored in the holder. The holder will get the name of the type of wands stored when you use it for the first time. It can be used for another type of wand once it is empty.

You can store up to 50 scrolls of the same type in this holder. Mind that this does not work with scribed scrolls, only the standard type you buy in stores.

Use the holder on a (stack) of scrolls to store them. You can also use the scroll holder on a container and you'll store all the suitable scrolls in it in one go.

Use the holder on yourself to recreate scrolls. It will produce stacks of 10 scrolls as long as you have 10 or more scrolls in your holder.

This description will be replaced by the number of scrolls stored in the holder. The holder will get the name of the type of scrolls stored when you use it for the first time. It can be used for another type of scrolls once it is empty.

You can store up to 50 mythals of the same type in this tube. 

Use the tube on a a mythal to store it. You can also use the mythal tube on a container and you'll store all the suitable mythals in it in one go.
For every 10 mythals this box will gain one mythal worth of weight, for example 10lbs for 10 lesser mythals. 

Use the tube on yourself to recreate mythals.

This description will be replaced by the number of mythals stored in the tube. The tube will get the name of the type of mythals stored when you use it for the first time.

You can store up to 100 bandages of the same strength in this bag. 

Use the bag on a (stack) of bandages to store them. You can also use the bandage bag on a container and you'll store all the suitable bandages in it in one go.
For every 20 bandages this box will gain 5 lbs in weight. 

Use the bag on yourself to recreate bandages. As long as you have over 6 bandages in the bag you'll recreate 5 bandages in one go.

This description will be replaced by the number of bandages stored in the bag. The bag will get the name of the type of bandages stored when you use it for the first time.
